His actual date of birth is unknown. When he emigrated from Russia to Canada in 1921, he did not speak English, and according to his daughter Janet Solberg June 23 was the first date that popped into his head when the immigration officer asked him when he was born. (Smith, pp.93, 542) Smith identifies October as a best guess, since the only specifics given were that he was born &quot;right after the first snows in 1909&quot;. (Smith, pp.93, 542)↩
