In Canadian politics, if a minority government &lt;U+2013&gt; one that does not have a majority of the elected members in the House of Commons &lt;U+2013&gt; loses a vote of non-confidence, than the government has to call a general election. This is exactly the scenario that happened in 1963, and why Lewis had to fight another election so soon after being elected.↩
